parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the ABS light illuminates
the vehicle vibrates or makes a metal-to-metal noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS pressure modulator can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to loss of stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the ABS system fails to function
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle vibrates or makes a metal-to-metal noise when applying the brakes.

symptoms: The brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy

loss of power steering and braking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine mounts can cause the engine to shift or move excessively, leading to loss of control, accidents, or engine damage.
symptoms: Engine mounts came out of the chassis while driving
causing the vehicle to become unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine idling issues can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine idled excessively when stopping at a traffic light
causing the driver to put the vehicle in neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warping of the upper intake manifold can cause gasket failure, leading to engine failure and loss of power.
symptoms: Upper intake manifold warped
causing gasket failure and engine stoppage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and electrical issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle cut off while driving
and all interior lights remained on; hesitation upon accelerating from a stop
accompanied by clicking and banging noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause serious damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle caught on fire while driving
with smoke and flames coming from the engine compartment; radiator or transmission failure may have contributed to the fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, including fires, stalling, and loss of critical vehicle functions, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or strand the driver.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from the steering column or electrical wires
shorted-out turn signals
failure to start
stalling while driving
blown fuses
and warning lights or indicators not functioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Alternator failure
battery drain
stalling
and loss of electrical power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch module failure can prevent the vehicle from starting, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Unable to start the vehicle
ignition switch module failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuse failure can cause critical vehicle functions to fail, including tail lights and flashers, increasing the risk of accidents.
